-- Former Malaysia Premier Mahathir Hospitalized in Melbourne, Bernama Says
-- B y   S o r a y a   P e r m a t a s a r i
-- 2010-10-02T15:42:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-02/former-malaysia-premier-mahathir-hospitalized-in-melbourne-bernama-says.html
Former Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad was admitted to a hospital in Melbourne today
for chest infection, Bernama reported, citing a statement.  His condition is stable and he will remain in the hospital
for a few days for observation, according to the state news
agency. Mahathir was in Melbourne to attend a seminar on human
development organized by the UMNO Club at the University of
Melbourne, Bernama said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Soraya Permatasari at 
 soraya@bloomberg.net  